@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

@{B}                      - - --÷{· @{BG SHADOW}@{APEN 2}  MP3 TAG@{BG HIGHLIGHT}@{APEN 1}ger v1.3  @{BG BACKGROUND} ·}÷-- - -

                         @{B}  ·       @{U}INTRODUCTION@{UU}        · @{UB}

   There's no point in ignoring the truth: MP3 Audio files are getting
   more and more popular on the Amiga every day. Since we Amigians never
   (want to) leg behind, many coders program several utilities to play,
   encode, manipulate these MP3 Audio files. Yet when we were searching
   for a program that allows you to change the information inside MP3's,
   we only found programs which were intended to be CLI-only.

   At this point we decided to program a small utility with a GUI to
   change the information inside MP3's (also referred to as @{i}MP3 TAG@{ui} info).

   So here it is, the first (as far as we know) MP3 TAG editor with a GUI
   for the Amiga computer, which wasn't intended to be CLI-only ;)

   @{u}Features of MP3 Tagger v1.3:@{uu}

   * Written in 100% 680x0 assembler.

   * Completely controllable through the GUI.

   * Does not use MUI (Magic User Interface).

   * Allows reading, editing, writing and erasing of MP3 Tags.

   * Complete font-sensitive GUI

   * No CLI interaction needed at all (but is supported).

   * Up-to-date list of MP3 Genres.

   We would like to remark that this program was not intended as a replacement
   for any other MP3 TAG editors out there and the idea was not stolen from
   any other TAG editor. This program has been in development for 3 months now,
   way before any recent TAG editor was released ;). It was first intended to
   be a GUI for the MP3Info program, but we decided to use our own code for
   editing the TAG's.

   Enjoy!

   The Faeries Geneses coders.

@ENDNODE

