   @{b}@{u}OTHER PROJECTS@{ub}@{uu}

   Other projects currently in development:

    * @{b}conversion.library@{ub} (99,9% finished)
      Easier converting of numbers from ascii <-> hex, dec, oct, bin
      for asm and c programmers.

    * @{b}PSX\miga@{ub} (50% finished)
      Sony Playstation development package for the Amiga. Includes R3000A assembler,
      conversion tools and programmer's docs.

    * @{b}Mogaira@{ub} (30% finished)
      Converts autodocs to amigaguide files, .i includes to .h includes, fd files
      to pragma & protos files.

    * @{b}ww_Addnote@{ub} (50% finished)
      Adds footnotes to WordWorth documents faster and more confortable.

   @{b}@{u}THE EQUIPMENT@{ub}@{uu}

   This package was completely created on Amiga International's(1)
   Amiga(2) 4000 and 1200 computers, using the following software:
    - Devpac(3) v3.14  : For writing and assembling the code.
    - MonAm(3)  v3.06  : For debugging and testing stuff.
    - PolyED(4) v2.29  : For writing all document files.

   We used the following references:
    - Amiga(2) Developper CD v1.1 (May 1996)
    - AMIGA(2) ROM Kernel Reference Manual: Libraries (Third edition)


